  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice B is correct. The dot plot gives the diameter, to the nearest inch, of each sea star in a group of tide pools. The number of dots above a given diameter represents the number of sea stars with that diameter, to the nearest inch. There are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"6\"><mn>6</mn></math> dots above <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"16\"><mn>16</mn></math> inches. Therefore, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"6\"><mn>6</mn></math> sea stars had a diameter, to the nearest inch, of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"16\"><mn>16</mn></math> inches.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice A is incorrect and may result from calculation or conceptual errors.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice C is incorrect. This is the number of sea stars with a diameter, to the nearest inch, of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"17\"><mn>17</mn></math> inches, not <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"16\"><mn>16</mn></math> inches.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice D is incorrect. This is the number of sea stars with a diameter, to the nearest inch, of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"18\"><mn>18</mn></math> inches, not <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"16\"><mn>16</mn></math> inches.</p>",
